</taxonomicNameLabel>
was described from two males. 
<bibRefCitation id="953D4B77970BE363F281FF0C02E1079A" author="Rothschild" box="[994,1199,151,176]" pageId="8" pageNumber="239" refString="Rothschild, W. (1912) New Syntomidae. Novitates Zoologicae, 19 (2), 151 - 186." type="journal article" year="1912">Rothschild (1912)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned that both already had the wings considerably worn by the time they were described. 
<bibRefCitation id="953D4B77970BE363F285FF2602ED07FE" author="Hampson" box="[998,1187,188,212]" pageId="8" pageNumber="239" refString="Hampson, G. F. (1914) Catalogue of the Lepidoptera Phalaenae in the British Museum, Supplement. vol. I. Catalogue of the Amatidae and Arctiadae (Nolinae and Lithosianae) in the collection of the British Museum. Printed by the order of the Trustees of the British Museum, London, 858 pp." type="book" year="1914">Hampson (1914)</bibRefCitation>
thought the specimen from La Unión was a female, and designated the other, from Pambilar, 
<collectingCountry id="89BB7616970BE363F2DDFF44025307D2" box="[958,1053,223,248]" name="Ecuador" pageId="8" pageNumber="239">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
, as the 
<typeStatus id="2E178824970BE363F511FF44029507D2" box="[1138,1243,223,248]" pageId="8" pageNumber="239">lectotype</typeStatus>
, even though the Peruvian specimen held a handwritten 
<typeStatus id="2E178824970BE363F32FFE9E04320637" box="[588,636,261,285]" pageId="8" pageNumber="239">type</typeStatus>
label with Rothschild's handwrinting. Nevertheless, Hampson's (1914) 
<typeStatus id="2E178824970BE363F1F4FEBC06B0066A" box="[151,254,295,320]" pageId="8" pageNumber="239">lectotype</typeStatus>
designation is valid.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F1133686970BE363F1A4FED7042F0532" blockId="8.[151,1436,151,717]" pageId="8" pageNumber="239">
This species is close to 
<taxonomicName id="36AC4D05970BE363F089FED60573064E" authority="(Druce, 1897)" authorityName="Druce" authorityYear="1897" baseAuthorityName="Druce" baseAuthorityYear="1897" box="[490,829,332,356]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Episcepsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="239" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="moloneyi">
<emphasis id="C3D8EA94970BE363F089FED604CC064E" box="[490,642,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="239">E. moloneyi</emphasis>
(Druce, 1897)
</taxonomicName>
(described from 
<collectingRegion id="3368F864970BE363F56EFED7021B064F" box="[1037,1109,332,357]" country="Belize" name="Belize" pageId="8" pageNumber="239">
<collectingCountry id="89BB7616970BE363F56EFED7021B064F" box="[1037,1109,332,357]" name="Belize" pageId="8" pageNumber="239">Belize</collectingCountry>
</collectingRegion>
and figured in the original description, pl. 72, fig. 16; by 
<bibRefCitation id="953D4B77970BE363F088FEEB04EE06A2" author="Hampson" box="[491,672,368,392]" pageId="8" pageNumber="239" refString="Hampson, G. F. (1898) Catalogue of the Lepidoptera Phalaenae in the British Museum, vol. I: Catalogue of the Syntomidae in the collection of the British Museum. Printed by the order of the Trustees of the British Museum, London, xxi + 559 pp., foldout phylogeny chart, 285 figs., pls. 1 - 17." type="book chapter" year="1898">Hampson, 1898</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 197; and by Draudt, 1915, pl. 20, row d) and 
<taxonomicName id="36AC4D05970BE363F5B6FEEA06810686" authority="Schaus, 1910" authorityName="Schaus" authorityYear="1910" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Episcepsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="239" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sixola">
<emphasis id="C3D8EA94970BE363F5B6FEEA037906A2" box="[1237,1335,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="239">E. sixola</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="953D4B77970BE363F426FEF406810686" author="Schaus" pageId="8" pageNumber="239" refString="Schaus, W. (1910) Descriptions of new Heterocera from Costa Rica. Annals and Magazine of Natural History, 8 (6), 189 - 211. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222931008692838" type="journal article" year="1910">Schaus, 1910</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(described from 
<collectingCountry id="89BB7616970BE363F0EDFE0F04450687" box="[398,523,404,429]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="8" pageNumber="239">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
, figured in 
<bibRefCitation id="953D4B77970BE363F3EAFE0E05730686" author="Hampson" box="[649,829,404,428]" pageId="8" pageNumber="239" refString="Hampson, G. F. (1914) Catalogue of the Lepidoptera Phalaenae in the British Museum, Supplement. vol. I. Catalogue of the Amatidae and Arctiadae (Nolinae and Lithosianae) in the collection of the British Museum. Printed by the order of the Trustees of the British Museum, London, 858 pp." type="book" year="1914">Hampson, 1914</bibRefCitation>
, pl. 13, fig. 5 and Draudt, 1915: pl. 28, row k), both of which seem to belong to a monophyletic concept of 
<taxonomicName id="36AC4D05970BE363F391FE23052606E5" authorityName="Butler" authorityYear="1877" box="[754,872,440,463]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Episcepsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="239" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C3D8EA94970BE363F391FE23052606E5" box="[754,872,440,463]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="239">Episcepsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, given the similarities observed in male genitalia (pers. obs.).These species share with 
<taxonomicName id="36AC4D05970BE363F35BFE4604EB06DE" authorityName="Pinheiro &amp; Araujo Junior" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Pinheiro &amp; Araujo Junior" baseAuthorityYear="2017" box="[568,677,476,500]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Episcepsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="239" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fumata" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="C3D8EA94970BE363F35BFE4604EB06DE" box="[568,677,476,500]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="239">E. fumata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="D8EB57EF970BE363F3CFFE47056306DF" box="[684,813,476,501]" pageId="8" pageNumber="239">
<emphasis id="C3D8EA94970BE363F3CFFE47056306DF" bold="true" box="[684,813,476,501]" pageId="8" pageNumber="239">comb. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
the red spots on tegulae, and the sparse white scales on proximal and medial areas of hindwings.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F1133686970BE363F1A4FDBE04BE05E7" blockId="8.[151,1436,151,717]" pageId="8" pageNumber="239">
<taxonomicName id="36AC4D05970BE363F1A4FDBE07D60516" authorityName="Pinheiro &amp; Araujo Junior" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Pinheiro &amp; Araujo Junior" baseAuthorityYear="2017" box="[199,408,548,572]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Episcepsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="239" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fumata" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="C3D8EA94970BE363F1A4FDBE07D60516" box="[199,408,548,572]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="239">Episcepsis fumata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="D8EB57EF970BE363F0C7FDBF04670517" box="[420,553,548,573]" pageId="8" pageNumber="239">
<emphasis id="C3D8EA94970BE363F0C7FDBF04670517" bold="true" box="[420,553,548,573]" pageId="8" pageNumber="239">comb. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
is easily distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="36AC4D05970BE363F2EBFDBE05BE0516" authorityName="Schaus" authorityYear="1910" box="[904,1008,548,572]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Episcepsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="239" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sixola">
<emphasis id="C3D8EA94970BE363F2EBFDBE05BE0516" box="[904,1008,548,572]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="239">E. sixola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="36AC4D05970BE363F552FDBE02F20516" baseAuthorityName="Druce" baseAuthorityYear="1897" box="[1073,1212,548,572]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Episcepsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="239" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="moloneyi">
<emphasis id="C3D8EA94970BE363F552FDBE02F20516" box="[1073,1212,548,572]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="239">E. moloneyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the absence of iridescent scales (present in both of the latter), and by the many white spots on various parts of the body. 
<taxonomicName id="36AC4D05970BE363F44BFDD3074A05AE" authorityName="Pinheiro &amp; Araujo Junior" authorityYear="2017" pageId="8" pageNumber="239" rank="subSpecies" status="comb. nov." subSpecies="fumata">
Moreover, 
<emphasis id="C3D8EA94970BE363F1F4FDF6074A05AE" box="[151,260,620,644]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="239">E. fumata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="D8EB57EF970BE363F069FDF707C405AF" box="[266,394,620,645]" pageId="8" pageNumber="239">
<emphasis id="C3D8EA94970BE363F069FDF707C405AF" bold="true" box="[266,394,620,645]" pageId="8" pageNumber="239">comb. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
is known only from high and moderate altitudes from Ecuatorian and Peruvian Andes, while the above mentioned species are from Central America. The apparently restricted distribution may explain the rarity of 
<taxonomicName id="36AC4D05970BE363F19AFD2E078A05E6" authorityName="Pinheiro &amp; Araujo Junior" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Pinheiro &amp; Araujo Junior" baseAuthorityYear="2017" box="[249,452,692,716]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Episcepsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="239" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fumata" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="C3D8EA94970BE363F19AFD2E078A05E6" box="[249,452,692,716]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="239">Episcepsis fumata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="D8EB57EF970BE363F0A8FD2F040505E7" box="[459,587,692,717]" pageId="8" pageNumber="239">
<emphasis id="C3D8EA94970BE363F0A8FD2F040505E7" bold="true" box="[459,587,692,717]" pageId="8" pageNumber="239">comb. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
in collections.
</paragraph>
